&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Invoca&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Invoca is an AI-powered revenue execution platform that brings together marketing, commerce, and contact center teams to turn every customer interaction into measurable, profitable growth. Join our dynamic, fast-growing team, where innovation and collaboration are at the core of our culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity: Architecting Invoca&#39;s Platform Foundation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Invoca accelerates the modernization of its platform—moving from a monolith to a service-oriented architecture leveraging IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS solutions—we are adopting a Platform as a Service strategy. This is a high-impact role where you will be instrumental in building the scalable, reliable, and widely-adopted technical foundations for our entire engineering organization. Your success will directly translate into improved engineering velocity, reduced technical debt, and clear alignment between platform investments and core business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a key member of the Architecture team, partnering directly with the Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) and Developer Enablement teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Builds, maintains, and supports the tooling, gems, libraries, CI/CD, and foundational services (like Identity) that all Invoca services rely on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SRE:&lt;/strong&gt; Provides the core infrastructure, observability, and stability to enable engineering teams to build new services and scale our platform effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role and Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Platform Technical Product Manager (TPM) to partner with technical leadership to define the strategy, roadmap, and execution for our internal platform capabilities. This role requires a systems mindset, sitting at the intersection of engineering, architecture, and product to build scalable, reliable, and reusable platform services that power our product ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner closely with Engineering, Infrastructure, Security, Data, and Product teams to ensure our platform enables fast innovation, high system reliability, and long-term scalability. This is a highly technical role that requires deep systems thinking, strong execution skills, and the ability to translate business needs into robust technical solutions.&amp;nbsp; You will report to the Director of Product &amp;amp; Engineering Operations in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform Strategy &amp;amp; Vision:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner to define and drive the vision, strategy, and roadmap for core platform services (e.g., APIs, infrastructure, identity, observability, internal tooling), ensuring platform investments directly align with company-level product and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Debt &amp;amp; Velocity:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively identify and champion opportunities to reduce technical debt, improve platform scalability, and accelerate overall development velocity across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with engineering leaders to define architectural direction and platform standards. Collaborate with Product Managers and other stakeholders to understand platform dependencies and drive alignment across multiple engineering teams. Work closely with security, compliance, and platform teams to ensure platform reliability and governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap &amp;amp; Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Translate platform strategy into clear, prioritized roadmaps and technical requirements (product briefs, epics, user stories). Define and track success metrics, including SLAs, performance benchmarks, and interna

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Invoca&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Invoca is the leading AI-native platform that enables marketing, sales, customer experience, and contact center teams to understand and act on the information within every customer interaction. By revealing intent across voice, SMS, and digital channels, Invoca helps enterprises drive better customer experiences, increase revenue, and operate with confidence at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a fast-growing company with a strong product culture, deep technical ambition, and a commitment to building AI systems that are reliable, transparent, and outcome-driven.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Layer That Makes AI Work in Production — and the Intelligence Products Built on Top of It&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In AI, the model is a commodity. The context is the moat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Invoca sits on one of the richest datasets in enterprise SaaS — millions of revenue-driving customer conversations across industries, channels, and buying journeys. The Data Platform team turns that data into the context layer that powers our AI agents and into intelligence products that customers and internal teams use to make better decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
